<br>
EDIT - Also, these are not Garadans, but Garans. The 6e creatures that prevent the prevention of energy loss. There are only 4 shadow creatures. One Dark Furok, and 3 Chaos Pliths. Please read the deck listing before reviewing.<br>
<br>
.... I don&#39;t have a god-forsaken Rayje&#39;s Belt, and I CAN&#39;T GET ANY. Stop telling me I need them!<br>
<br>
While your at it, why not look at Tainted Lore: Darkening Shadows, the revised version of this deck.<br>
<br>
Evil Evu&#39;s main usefullness is as a card-drawing engine. If you can manage to keep a Chaos Plith or two in play with a Pruitt&#39;s Robe, Energy Band, or just a couple of Grow&#39;s.. you&#39;ll have a tremendous card advantage in no time. I&#39;ve won games where I&#39;ve held my entire deck in my hand..<br>
<br>
One caution.. only play some of your important relics if you think Evu has a good chance of sticking around for a while<br>
<br>
Next in the lineup would be Zannah, arguably the best Magi available. By now, from Evu, you should have a Relic-Stalker or two in your hand. Save those for any Rayje&#39;s Belts and or Swords that might make their appearance. One nice thing you can do with her, is to &#39;boots in a Giant Carillion, throw it into your opponant&#39;s second largest creature, then &#39;stomp&#39; his biggest. Toss in a RoV&#39;d Weebo, and keep the fun rolling.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Next, we have a choice between Zajan and Pruitt.. I tend to use Zajan just because he&#39;s a fun little guy, and the cards he draws in the beginning of the turn is sometimes just enough to give you the game. Pruitt is the other choice because she can get downright nasty when combined with the robe she starts with.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
Remember, Naroom Magi can play with Dark Furoks and Chaos Pliths.. If you&#39;ve got the energy to spare, they&#39;re better then the counterparts.     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
